data.content:
Let me tell you a brief about this role. The Patient Experience Representative in our units play a vital role in ensuring a 
seamless patient journey. This position focuses on patient encounter management by 
delivering exceptional customer service, collaborating with referring providers, and securing 
necessary authorizations to manage patient and staff schedules effectively. Responsibilities 
also include check-in and check-out tasks, where the representative greets and directs patients 
and families, monitors daily schedules, reconciles payments, and facilitates communication 
with financial counseling. Additionally, the role encompasses administrative duties such as 
recording and forwarding messages, triaging urgent calls, and providing clerical support for 
admissions, discharges, and transfers, including updating patient monitoring systems. Overall, 
the representative ensures a positive experience for patients while supporting unit operations. Does that all sound good?

And, just before this call ends, I wanted to share what makes this role so exciting. 
Boston Children’s Hospital is one of the top children’s hospitals in the country. Patients come 
here from all over the world to receive the care we provide, and everyone, from our clinical and 
research staff, support roles like environmental and food services, and administrative staff, are 
all passionate and focused on helping sick children get well. As a patient experience 
representative, you will be the face of the department you support, assisting patients and 
setting the tone for their visit. How does that sound?

Great! That concludes the questions I have for you. We’ll share your information with 
our recruiters and hiring managers who will decide if they want to move forward. If they do, a 
BCH Talent Acquisition representative will reach out to get you scheduled for next steps.  This 
may be a zoom call or in person interview.  If you are being moved to interview, you will also 
receive a link to our reference check website so that you can start entering your references. You
will need 4 total, at least 2 of which should be from current or former managers.  We send 
references before scheduling interviews to expedite the interview process for you. Have a good one, Bye!
